---
import Block from '../components/Block.astro';
import List from '../components/List.astro';
import ListItem from '../components/ListItem.astro';
import Paragraph from '../components/Paragraph.astro';
import Text from '../components/Text.astro';
import Title from '../components/Title.astro';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy">
    <Title
        heading="1"
        title="Privacy Policy"
    />
    <Block>
        <Title
            heading="2"
            title="About"
        />
        <Paragraph>
            <Text
                >This Privacy Policy defines how your data is used when you use our extension.</Text
            >
            <Text>Last Updated: Sept 23th, 2022.</Text>
        </Paragraph>
    </Block>
    <Block>
        <Title
            heading="2"
            title="Definitions"
        />
        <Paragraph>
            <List>
                <Text>These definitions apply regardless of capitalization or quantity.</Text>
                <ListItem
                    ><b>Developer</b>, <b>Publisher</b>, <b>Us</b>, <b>We</b> refers to the contributor(s),
                    creator(s), and maintainer(s) of this extension</ListItem
                >
                <ListItem><b>Extension</b> refers to Shorts Deflector</ListItem>
                <ListItem><b>Handle</b> refers to the possession and usage of data</ListItem>
                <ListItem
                    ><b>Third party</b> is as defined in article four of the General Data Protection
                    Regulation (GDPR)</ListItem
                >
            </List>
        </Paragraph>
    </Block>
    <Block>
        <Title
            heading="2"
            title="What Data Does This Extension Collect?"
        />
        <Paragraph>
            <List>
                <Text>This extension collects and handles the following data by default:</Text>
                <ListItem>Tab information (tab Id, URL)</ListItem>
                <ListItem>YouTube site content</ListItem>
                <ListItem>User input to this extension's user interface</ListItem>
            </List>
        </Paragraph>
        <Paragraph>
            <List>
                <Text
                    >If you opt into the enhanced performance option, then the following data is
                    also collected:</Text
                >
                <ListItem>All site content (excluding local files and protected webpages)</ListItem>
            </List>
        </Paragraph>
    </Block>
    <Block>
        <Title
            heading="2"
            title="How Does This Extension Collect Your Data?"
        />
        <Paragraph>
            <Text
                >This extension collects some data through APIs provided by your browser. For
                example, when you load a webpage, your browser tells this extension that a webpage
                has loaded and provides information such as a tab Id and URL. This content is
                collected even if automatic although this data is then thrown out almost
                immediately.</Text
            >
            <Text
                >On YouTube webpages, if automatic redirecting is enabled, a script will find and
                get all links present on that page. If you opt into the enhanced performance option,
                the scope increases from just YouTube webpages to all webpages (excluding local
                files and protected webpages).</Text
            >
            <Text
                >User inputs are collected when you change a setting with the toggles on this
                extension's popup.</Text
            >
        </Paragraph>
    </Block>
    <Block>
        <Title
            heading="2"
            title="How Does This Extension Use Your Data?"
        />
        <Paragraph>
            <Text
                >All data collected by this extension is for the express purpose of redirecting or
                changing YouTube Shorts pages.</Text
            >
            <Text
                >Tab information is used to detect when you load a new webpage, to test if it is a
                YouTube Shorts page, and to test if you want this extension to be active on that
                page. Site content is used to replace YouTube Shorts URLs to normal YouTube links
                and to replace the Shorts icon on thumbnails. Settings are used to modify the
                extension's behavior and keep track of your preferences.</Text
            >
            <Text
                >No data collected listed above is used for analytics, monitoring, logging, or
                similar. This extension does not share anything with the developers/publisher, nor
                any third parties.</Text
            >
        </Paragraph>
    </Block>
    <Block>
        <Title
            heading="2"
            title="How Does This Extension Store Your Data?"
        />
        <Paragraph>
            <Text
                >If you are signed into your browser, then extension settings may be synced to your
                browser. Otherwise, settings are kept in local storage. Contact your browser's
                support to learn how you can remove this data. Usually, your can clear this data
                from your browser's settings.</Text
            >
            <Text
                >All other data is ephemeral and only exists temporarily; nothing other than
                extension settings is stored in a permanent state.</Text
            >
        </Paragraph>
    </Block>
    <Block>
        <Title
            heading="2"
            title="Changes to Our Privacy Policy"
        />
        <Paragraph>
            <Text
                >We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. The date at the top will be
                updated if we do so. These changes are effective immediately, after they are posted
                on this page.</Text
            >
        </Paragraph>
    </Block>
    <Block>
        <Title
            heading="2"
            title="Contact"
        />
        <Paragraph>
            <Text
                >If you have any questions about this extension's Privacy Policy or the data we hold
                on you, please do not hesitate to contact us at <a
                    class="bold text-light-1 dark:text-dark-1"
                    href="mailto:attituding@outlook.com">attituding@outlook.com</a
                >.</Text
            >
        </Paragraph>
    </Block>
</Base>
